{
  "id": "smallhold-z8j",
  "title": "Phase 3: OAuth2 + Client Reads",
  "description": "Implement just enough OAuth2 for Mastodon clients to authenticate, plus all Tier 1 read endpoints. The authorization flow is: admin logs in with password, picks which persona this token should authenticate as, submits. No per-user accounts. After this phase, Ivory or Elk should be able to log in, land on an empty home timeline, and see the profile.",
  "design": "Minimal OAuth2: only app registration, authorize, token exchange, revoke. Token: 64 random bytes base64url, stored as SHA-256 hex. Never log tokens. admin CLI mint-token command for scripting. Scopes: read, write, follow, push (push ignored). Authorization page: minimal HTML form.",
  "acceptance_criteria": "Ivory can log in against the instance and land on the home timeline; GET /api/v1/accounts/verify_credentials returns correct account object; all Tier 1 empty-array endpoints (filters, lists, custom_emojis, etc.) return empty arrays with correct shapes; bearer token middleware rejects invalid tokens with 401",
  "status": "closed",
